WEBVTT

00:20.562 --> 00:22.563
( jet approaching )

00:24.566 --> 00:26.567
( man speaking over radio )

00:49.216 --> 00:50.717
( chuckles )

00:58.767 --> 01:00.476
( car alarm chirps )

01:40.434 --> 01:42.185
( girl clears throat )

01:46.774 --> 01:48.357
Listen. Um...

01:49.860 --> 01:52.820
l had a great time
sitting next to you on the plane.

02:02.289 --> 02:04.582
Silver Lake, right?

02:17.638 --> 02:19.722
( pop music playing )

03:36.216 --> 03:38.509
Girl:
"Every morning as l drive away

03:38.677 --> 03:40.344
l am reaching back for you.

03:40.512 --> 03:42.221
lt is a helpless feeling,

03:42.389 --> 03:44.724
this wishing, this wanting,

03:44.892 --> 03:46.726
this knowing you will arrive

03:46.894 --> 03:49.687
just minutes after l have gone."

03:51.356 --> 03:54.150
Well, l thought that
was really freakin' good.

03:55.694 --> 03:57.987
Teacher: All right.
All in favor of including this piece

03:58.155 --> 04:00.072
in our spring issue, raise your hand.

04:03.577 --> 04:05.244
Nearly unanimous.

04:05.412 --> 04:08.080
And our author-- Kolt.

04:08.248 --> 04:10.917
Sylvia Plath would be proud.

04:11.919 --> 04:13.961
Congratulations.

04:19.760 --> 04:21.218
( exhales sharply )

04:24.890 --> 04:27.266
Thanks, dude.

04:32.022 --> 04:33.105
- Hi.
- Hey.

04:33.273 --> 04:36.275
- Um, hello. l'm Martine.
- Hello.

04:36.443 --> 04:38.110
- Hey. Hi. ( chuckles )
- l'm Peter.

04:38.278 --> 04:40.154
- Let me grab this for you. Come on in.
- Thanks.

04:40.322 --> 04:41.948
Julie can't wait to meet you.

04:47.955 --> 04:50.122
What's making you feel so powerless?

04:51.458 --> 04:53.250
l'm way too afraid

04:53.418 --> 04:56.379
to even approach a woman
that might be on my intellectual level.

04:56.546 --> 04:58.589
l know what you're gonna say.

04:58.757 --> 05:01.384
lt's not 'cause
l'm afraid she'll reject me.

05:02.427 --> 05:04.136
l'm afraid l'll reject her.

05:05.138 --> 05:07.139
Okay. Why is that?

05:08.558 --> 05:11.978
You know, a lot of smart women
think too much to look good

05:12.145 --> 05:14.480
and talk too much to fuck well.

05:16.358 --> 05:19.151
l feel like such an asshole saying
these things to a woman.

05:20.445 --> 05:22.905
l do get what you're saying, actually.

05:25.492 --> 05:27.326
'Cause the movie
comes out this week,

05:27.494 --> 05:30.246
everyone's acting like l'm supposed
to be excited, but l fucking hate it.

05:30.414 --> 05:32.999
And l wish l could say it looks nothing
like the script l handed them...

05:34.167 --> 05:36.127
but they didn't change
a goddamn line.

05:36.294 --> 05:38.379
l just wrote something
that isn't very good.

05:38.547 --> 05:40.798
We're gonna need to stop.

05:40.966 --> 05:43.134
( groans )
Don't do this to me, Julie.

05:43.301 --> 05:45.344
l will see you on Wednesday.

05:51.476 --> 05:53.477
( silent )

06:20.922 --> 06:23.132
There's a lot of life
that'll come out with the sound.

06:23.300 --> 06:26.010
There's-- you know,
like the bug's footsteps

06:26.178 --> 06:28.054
or maybe his breath.

06:28.221 --> 06:31.640
You know, what would it sound like
if you could hear the bug's heartbeat?

06:31.808 --> 06:34.935
Or, like, heartache.
What would that sound like?

06:35.103 --> 06:36.520
- ( chuckles )
- You know?

06:36.688 --> 06:38.397
Peter: Yeah.

06:38.565 --> 06:40.483
All right.
l think this'll be fun.

06:40.650 --> 06:43.235
Martine:
Yeah. l'm really excited.

06:45.906 --> 06:48.866
Thank you so much for putting aside time
to do this with me.

06:49.034 --> 06:50.451
- Absolutely.
- So you're working on, like,

06:50.619 --> 06:52.036
a big studio movie right now?

06:52.204 --> 06:54.246
l am, yeah.
They're not picture-locked yet.

06:55.999 --> 06:57.166
So you're in luck.

06:59.086 --> 07:03.214
Hey, Peter, is this
a take-from-the-fruit-bowl night?

07:03.381 --> 07:05.716
Martine, this is Kolt.
Kolt, Martine.

07:05.884 --> 07:07.009
- Martine: Hi.
- Hey.

07:07.177 --> 07:10.429
What is
a take-from-the-fruit-bowl night?

07:10.597 --> 07:13.432
Oh, it just means that
everyone's on their own for dinner.

07:13.600 --> 07:15.559
Nobody's taken
responsibility as of yet.

07:15.727 --> 07:16.936
( chuckles )

07:17.104 --> 07:19.271
Peter:
That's a maybe?

07:40.877 --> 07:43.462
- Hey, David.
- Oh hey, Kolt.

07:44.464 --> 07:45.714
Hey.

07:46.758 --> 07:48.676
l'm just getting out of here.

07:50.804 --> 07:52.596
Crazy plans?

07:53.890 --> 07:55.891
David:
Just finishing up some things for Peter.

07:56.893 --> 07:58.310
How about you?

07:58.478 --> 08:00.563
Lots of homework?

08:00.730 --> 08:04.608
Not really. l already did
this history thing that's due Friday.

08:05.819 --> 08:07.528
Well, it's good not to procrastinate.

08:07.696 --> 08:09.321
( chuckles ) Yeah.

08:09.489 --> 08:11.323
l do anyway sometimes though.

08:11.491 --> 08:13.826
Procrastinate.

08:13.994 --> 08:16.787
Oh yeah, of course.
l'm giving you advice l can't take, so--

08:16.955 --> 08:18.664
( Kolt chuckles )

08:27.465 --> 08:30.134
- Eating bark in a tree.
- Peter: Slow or fast?

08:30.302 --> 08:31.552
Fast.

08:31.720 --> 08:34.722
Wind, and also sand
blowing in the wind.

08:36.683 --> 08:39.143
Sounds that only ants hear.

08:39.311 --> 08:40.686
Ah, need to be more specific.

08:40.854 --> 08:43.938
- You know what? We'll come back to it.
- Okay, gasping.

08:45.025 --> 08:47.193
Sticky stuff.

08:47.360 --> 08:49.153
Bowling pins.

08:49.321 --> 08:51.155
Blood on pavement.

08:51.323 --> 08:53.490
- Got it.
- Really?

08:53.658 --> 08:54.700
Hey, come on.

08:55.702 --> 08:56.869
An old train.

08:58.205 --> 09:01.790
Okay, um, bodies rubbing
up against each other.

09:03.001 --> 09:04.543
Okay. So people having sex?

09:05.629 --> 09:08.547
Yes. But not like--
( grunts )

09:08.715 --> 09:10.549
Okay. Good to know.

09:10.717 --> 09:12.635
( chuckles )

09:12.802 --> 09:14.803
( crickets chirping )

09:18.225 --> 09:20.684
( door opens, closes )

09:20.852 --> 09:22.811
- Hi, Dad.
- Hey, bud.

09:23.813 --> 09:26.357
- Hey.
- Hi.

09:26.524 --> 09:27.900
Julie:
ls she coming to eat? Where is she?

09:28.068 --> 09:29.568
- Jet lag.
- ls it gonna work out?

09:29.736 --> 09:31.862
l think so, yeah.
She's really sweet.

09:32.030 --> 09:33.739
- Good.
- l think she's really talented too.

09:35.575 --> 09:38.160
Hey, who is in the pool house?

09:38.328 --> 09:40.079
Her name is Martine

09:40.247 --> 09:42.706
and she is a friend
of my friend Miriam's,

09:42.874 --> 09:44.083
and she needed Daddy's help.

09:44.251 --> 09:45.668
- Hey, guess what.
- What?

09:45.835 --> 09:47.586
My poem got into lit mag.

09:47.754 --> 09:49.713
Julie:
Sweetness, that's fantastic.

09:49.881 --> 09:51.382
- Did you call your dad?
- Not yet.

09:51.549 --> 09:53.717
Well, you know, he wrote poems
before he wrote songs.

09:53.885 --> 09:56.553
And maybe one day he will publish
some of those poems,

09:56.721 --> 09:58.681
and he can buy us a hot tub.

09:59.724 --> 10:01.976
( camera shutter clicking )

10:15.365 --> 10:16.949
( sighs )

10:42.976 --> 10:45.561
( phone ringing )

10:49.232 --> 10:52.651
- Julie: Wanna get that?
- Huh-uh, no.

10:52.819 --> 10:55.654
- You sure?
- Yeah. One of the kids will get it.

10:55.822 --> 10:57.614
No, they won't.

10:57.782 --> 10:59.950
They always let it go to the machine.

11:00.118 --> 11:02.453
And you never check the machine.

11:02.620 --> 11:06.123
- ( ringing continues )
- Wait. l'm coming, l'm coming.

11:06.291 --> 11:08.500
Hello?

11:08.668 --> 11:11.545
- Hey, Avi.
- ( chuckles )

11:11.713 --> 11:15.007
No, l don't know where Sea Horse is.
Hold on, let me check.

11:18.136 --> 11:20.387
Kolt!
lt's Avi on line one.

11:20.555 --> 11:22.639
l don't want to talk to Avi, Peter.

11:22.807 --> 11:25.601
Okay, why don't you
tell him that yourself?

11:29.356 --> 11:31.106
- ( beeps )
- Firm hand of a parent.

11:31.274 --> 11:33.817
- Julie: Oh, so good.
- ( snaps fingers ) Nailed it.

11:44.037 --> 11:45.913
Get the arm in there.

11:51.836 --> 11:53.796
- Julie: l gotta wash my face.
- What?

11:53.963 --> 11:57.925
- l have to wash my face.
- All right, the TV's going back on.

11:58.093 --> 12:00.177
Them's the rules.

12:00.345 --> 12:03.389
- ( crowd cheering on TV )
- ( sneakers squeaking )

12:03.556 --> 12:06.058
( announcer speaks )

12:06.226 --> 12:07.810
( snapping)

12:07.977 --> 12:09.978
( snapping echoing )

12:11.523 --> 12:14.066
( Martine breathes deeply )

12:14.234 --> 12:16.193
( squishing )

12:17.195 --> 12:19.196
( squishing echoing )

12:22.742 --> 12:25.035
( popping, rustling )

12:25.203 --> 12:27.413
( echoing )

12:27.580 --> 12:30.040
( echoing intensifies,
crackling )

12:30.208 --> 12:31.667
( mimicking popping )

12:31.835 --> 12:33.961
( echoes, distorted )

12:34.129 --> 12:35.879
( hisses, bubbling )

12:36.047 --> 12:38.298
( distorted bubbling )

12:38.466 --> 12:40.884
( distorted )

12:44.347 --> 12:46.515
( deep rhythmic thumping )

12:48.059 --> 12:51.270
( intensified )

12:51.438 --> 12:53.564
( school bell rings )

12:53.731 --> 12:56.191
Hey, where you going?
Class is that way.

12:56.359 --> 12:57.985
Oh, l'm not going.

13:15.920 --> 13:19.798
You want a section?
l don't read Science, Finance or Sports.

13:20.800 --> 13:22.843
Yeah, l'll take Science.

13:37.108 --> 13:40.903
So, um, how's it going with David?

13:43.281 --> 13:44.531
Hmm?

13:44.699 --> 13:48.494
Oh. Um, it's complicated.

13:50.997 --> 13:53.999
l mean,
there's definitely chemistry, you know?

13:54.167 --> 13:56.418
But the age difference.

13:58.296 --> 14:00.964
And he works for Peter, so--

14:02.217 --> 14:04.009
l think we're both just...

14:04.177 --> 14:06.929
a little afraid of where
it could go, you know?

14:09.474 --> 14:12.100
Well, it's good to be cautious.

14:12.268 --> 14:13.685
You have plenty of time.

14:13.853 --> 14:16.813
We're only, you know, 16.
( chuckles )

14:18.107 --> 14:21.193
( scoffs )
l hate it when people say that.

14:29.369 --> 14:31.370
( water lapping )

14:36.668 --> 14:39.670
( distorted )

14:44.217 --> 14:45.884
l don't know.
What do you think?

14:48.555 --> 14:51.348
Look, sir,
we don't need a pool cleaning.

14:51.516 --> 14:52.891
The pool is clean.

14:53.059 --> 14:54.851
- l'm looking at it right now.
- David.

14:56.854 --> 14:58.480
( scoffs )
No, you know what?

14:58.648 --> 15:00.899
Just forget it.
You're crooks anyway.

15:02.986 --> 15:04.903
My assistant.
He's a good guy.

15:11.494 --> 15:12.995
Dusty's been upset
about this dead lizard

15:13.162 --> 15:15.205
that's been clogging the drain
for like a week now,

15:15.373 --> 15:17.374
and l don't think
the issue's worth $600.

15:17.542 --> 15:21.295
Peter: This is our guest Martine.
She's the bug auteur.

15:21.462 --> 15:24.131
- lt's nice to meet you. Excuse me.
- ( water splashes )

15:25.592 --> 15:27.426
l love that guy.

15:27.594 --> 15:29.678
Every time we don't have
a big job going on,

15:29.846 --> 15:32.014
he just tries to fix
what's broken in life.

15:32.181 --> 15:34.266
My life.

15:36.269 --> 15:38.437
Okay, what's next? Chimes?

15:39.606 --> 15:41.481
( shower running )

15:54.746 --> 15:57.122
And that is the power
of directional microphones.

15:57.290 --> 15:58.999
They're kind of like magic wands.

15:59.167 --> 16:00.792
Here, come on.
l want to show you something.

16:04.922 --> 16:06.715
All right,
just lay down right here.

16:09.761 --> 16:11.720
Keep the headphones on.

16:15.642 --> 16:17.476
Close your eyes.

16:19.979 --> 16:23.440
You tell me--
what do you think you're hearing?

16:23.608 --> 16:25.484
- All right?
- Okay.

16:28.571 --> 16:30.322
- ( cars passing )
- ( rhythmic noise )

16:39.916 --> 16:42.417
l don't know.
That sounds like...

16:42.585 --> 16:45.504
a concert, but far away.

16:47.340 --> 16:48.340
lt's the highway.

16:48.508 --> 16:50.133
With those mountains in the back,

16:50.301 --> 16:52.177
it echoes through the entire canyon.

16:54.806 --> 16:56.515
- Wanna do another one?
- Yeah.

16:56.683 --> 16:59.101
Close your eyes.

16:59.268 --> 17:00.936
Okay, what about this one?

17:03.022 --> 17:05.022
( rubbing lightly )

17:11.280 --> 17:14.324
That sounds like wind
going through trees.

17:14.492 --> 17:16.159
l'll buy that.

17:20.373 --> 17:22.332
Okay.

17:26.838 --> 17:28.755
Tell me what you hear...

17:28.923 --> 17:30.465
now.

17:49.652 --> 17:51.236
( chuckles )

17:53.906 --> 17:56.658
- ( birds chirping )
- ( man speaking ltalian )

17:59.495 --> 18:01.246
But what kind?

18:11.299 --> 18:12.466
( scoffs )

18:14.510 --> 18:16.428
l'm tired.

18:23.895 --> 18:24.978
( man speaks ltalian )

18:28.733 --> 18:30.275
( correcting ltalian )

19:00.973 --> 19:02.474
David:
Hey, buddy.

19:02.642 --> 19:04.810
Hey!
Ah, you looking to brawl?

19:06.020 --> 19:08.563
You're Julie. Wow!

19:08.731 --> 19:10.565
- Can l hug you?
- Yeah,

19:10.733 --> 19:12.567
let's hug. l'm pro-hug.

19:14.529 --> 19:16.196
l can't believe it.
l'm meeting you--

19:16.364 --> 19:20.242
one of the original members
of Miriam's postfeminist wolf pack.

19:20.409 --> 19:22.327
l've seen pictures of you guys, like,

19:22.495 --> 19:25.372
sitting around swimming pools
looking focused.

19:25.540 --> 19:27.791
lt-it seems like it was an amazing time.

19:27.959 --> 19:29.668
- l don't know.
- Buonasera.

19:29.836 --> 19:31.837
- Peter: Ciao, guys.
- Hey, Kolt.

19:32.004 --> 19:35.841
Hi.

19:36.008 --> 19:38.927
Hi. l really like yourjeans.

19:40.179 --> 19:42.514
- Thanks.
- Do they have zippers on them?

19:42.682 --> 19:45.684
Um, yeah, they--
they do.

19:45.852 --> 19:48.270
- ( chuckles )
- Hey, you want to take off?

19:48.437 --> 19:49.938
Martine:
Uh, yeah, we should.

19:50.106 --> 19:52.190
He's taking me
to my friend's art opening.

19:53.359 --> 19:55.485
Yeah, l-l can't drive.

19:56.612 --> 19:58.238
l'm a New Yorker.
( laughs )

19:58.406 --> 20:00.866
l'm clinging to that as my excuse.

20:01.033 --> 20:02.868
- Can you drive?
- No.

20:03.035 --> 20:06.288
No, not yet.
But we will be practicing very soon.

20:06.455 --> 20:08.248
- Yes, we will.
- Okay.

20:08.416 --> 20:11.042
- You hungry, Sea Horse?
- Not really.

20:11.210 --> 20:12.878
Peter:
Hey, remember: 9:00 a.m. tomorrow,

20:13.045 --> 20:15.422
- actors.
- Yes. l will be there.

20:15.590 --> 20:18.008
And, Julie, l'm sorry that
we didn't get a chance to talk.

20:18.175 --> 20:19.301
- Oh, we will.
- Okay.

20:19.468 --> 20:22.137
Julie, is it possible to get my check?

20:22.305 --> 20:25.307
Yes. l'm so sorry.
l'll be right back.

20:26.350 --> 20:28.393
( car engine starts )

21:11.646 --> 21:14.230
( scoffs )
There is a mammal that lays eggs.

21:14.398 --> 21:16.983
Platypus, Avi! Platypus.

21:25.284 --> 21:26.910
l gotta go.

21:44.929 --> 21:46.596
( breathing deeply )

22:01.153 --> 22:03.905
( crickets chirping )

22:04.073 --> 22:06.074
( car approaches )

22:07.076 --> 22:08.994
( gearshift clicks )

22:09.161 --> 22:10.870
- ( engine stops )
- ( Martine exhales deeply )

22:15.001 --> 22:17.502
Thank you for coming with me tonight.

22:18.671 --> 22:20.422
No, thank you for bringing me.

22:43.821 --> 22:45.113
Um...

22:45.281 --> 22:47.198
l don't think

22:47.366 --> 22:50.577
that l should do this right now.

22:54.498 --> 22:55.874
Okay.

22:56.042 --> 22:59.044
l just-- l just got here.

22:59.211 --> 23:01.379
And l'm here to work.

23:01.547 --> 23:04.257
And l think it's smarter

23:04.425 --> 23:07.343
to forgo this type of--

23:09.722 --> 23:12.348
Anyway, this was really nice.

23:12.516 --> 23:14.517
Really nice.

23:30.951 --> 23:32.952
( both breathing heavily )

23:44.006 --> 23:46.007
( heavy breathing continues )

24:04.193 --> 24:06.111
( car door closes )

24:07.780 --> 24:09.739
- ( bangs )
- Ah!

24:09.907 --> 24:12.700
- ( cellphone ringing )
- Ah. ( hisses )

24:13.994 --> 24:15.411
Mmm.
( sighs )

24:15.579 --> 24:17.956
- Martine, you're alive.
- Doug. Hey.

24:18.124 --> 24:20.416
- Am l waking you up?
- Um-- God, no.

24:20.584 --> 24:22.961
l've been awake
for a couple hours already.

24:23.129 --> 24:26.464
- Everything going all right?
- Yeah, it's going great.

24:26.632 --> 24:29.175
( Doug speaks )

24:29.343 --> 24:32.846
Um, l haven't seen it yet,

24:33.013 --> 24:34.305
um...

24:34.473 --> 24:38.184
but as soon as l get my lnternet,

24:38.352 --> 24:40.562
- l'm gonna--
- ( Doug speaking )

24:40.729 --> 24:42.147
No. No no no no.

24:42.314 --> 24:45.150
Yeah, we'll definitely finish on time.

24:45.317 --> 24:46.609
Okay.

24:46.777 --> 24:48.319
All right. Talk to you later.

24:50.906 --> 24:55.410
Okay.

24:56.704 --> 24:57.954
( groans )

24:59.039 --> 25:00.665
Hi. l'm--

25:00.833 --> 25:02.750
l'm sorry l'm late. l, um--

25:02.918 --> 25:05.003
l couldn't find
the dialogue that l wrote.

25:05.171 --> 25:06.796
That's okay.

25:06.964 --> 25:09.340
Let's, uh, make
a couple copies of this.

25:09.508 --> 25:11.176
- Hi, l'm Martine.
- Hi.

25:11.343 --> 25:13.511
- Hi, nice to meet you.
- Thanks for coming, guys.

25:13.679 --> 25:15.805
- Sure.
- Whoo. Okay.

25:25.316 --> 25:26.858
Patient:
So the reviews are in.

25:28.944 --> 25:31.654
Some great, some good,
a few really hostile ones, of course.

25:31.822 --> 25:34.490
How are the reviews making you feel?

25:36.702 --> 25:38.494
l don't want to talk about the reviews.

25:38.662 --> 25:40.663
Okay.

25:42.625 --> 25:45.001
l had a dream last night.

25:45.169 --> 25:47.503
Another one about your grandmother?

25:47.671 --> 25:48.880
No.

25:49.048 --> 25:51.507
lt was about you.

25:52.927 --> 25:55.053
All right.

25:55.221 --> 25:57.472
- Am l allowed to tell you about it?
- Of course.

26:00.059 --> 26:01.976
Um, l was on set

26:02.144 --> 26:03.728
in the house that we shot in--

26:03.896 --> 26:06.064
that weird glass box in the Valley--

26:06.232 --> 26:09.651
and David Strathairn was
eating cereal out of a megaphone.

26:09.818 --> 26:12.070
( chuckles )

26:12.238 --> 26:15.573
l had a break. Something drew me
to one of the bedrooms.

26:15.741 --> 26:18.201
l opened the door--

26:18.369 --> 26:19.744
( clears throat )

26:19.912 --> 26:22.205
You were lying on the carpet,

26:22.373 --> 26:25.750
and, um, you were
all dressed up in full lingerie--

26:25.918 --> 26:28.711
you know, lacy bra, a thong, stockings,

26:28.879 --> 26:32.590
those things that you use
to clip your stockings to your panties.

